; rag-heal.fk — the self-healing memory loop as the recipe the kernel runs.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/adler32.fk form-stdlib/rag-key.fk form-stdlib/rag-freshness.fk
;
; The body is Form; the kernel is the runtime; no Python in this lane. The pure
; DECISIONS are already four-way + fkwu — the content key (rag-key.fk → 7), the
; freshness delta (rag-freshness.fk → 63), the retrieval depth (rag-adaptive-k.fk
; → 15), the ranking (rag-retrieve.fk → 31). This recipe is the host-io ORCHESTRATION
; over them: read a file through the kernel's host-io and key it, and sense whether a
; cached key still matches. host-read is the one crossing; the arithmetic stays Form.
;
; Host-io is non-deterministic, so this lane is kernel-witnessed (Go now; the
; fkwu-native exe is the platform step), NOT part of the four-way output floor —
; exactly as host-exec/host-read/host-write are documented in the kernel. The
; embedding step is a local-oracle model-door crossing (ollama via host-exec),
; ledgered by form-cli-membrane.fk; enumerating brand-new files needs a directory
; -list host-io op the kernel does not yet carry — that absorb path is the named
; gap, while drift and orphan healing are fully Form over host-read.
;
; host-read/host-write are Go-kernel + fkwu-native-exe builtins (the Rust/TS walkers
; do not carry them), so this lane is single-runtime by design, NOT in the fourth-arm
; manifest. Witness (writes a known text, reads+keys it back, senses fresh-vs-drift,
; all in Form on the kernel — zero Python; Go leg → 7):
;   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/adler32.fk \
;     form-stdlib/rag-key.fk form-stdlib/rag-freshness.fk form-stdlib/rag-heal.fk \
;     <a (do (host-write ...) (rk-text-key ...) (rh-file-key ...) ...) band>

(do
    ; the content key of a FILE: read via kernel host-io, then key the bytes in Form.
    (defn rh-file-key (path) (rk-text-key (host-read path)))

    ; is a cached key still the file's current key? (1 fresh, 0 drifted/missing)
    (defn rh-fresh? (path cached-key) (if (str_eq (rh-file-key path) cached-key) 1 0))

    ; sense one cell against the cache: a rag-freshness entry (id key) is stale when
    ; the file at `id` keys differently than the entry holds. Reuses rf-stale? — the
    ; same four-way delta logic, fed the file's live key through host-io.
    (defn rh-cell-stale? (id cached-key)
        (rf-stale? (rf-entry id (rh-file-key id))
                   (list (rf-entry id cached-key))))

    0)
